2020 Media Pluralism Monitor.

                     

                  
 

                     
   
In December 2018, a bomb attack on the SKAI TV station in Athens caused extensive damage. In May 2019, the car of a reporter for CNN Greece reporter was destroyed in an arson attack. The European Centre for Press and Media Freedom (ECPMF) reports that, also in 2019, anarchists stormed into the headquarters of the newspaper Athens Voice and smashed office equipment, computers and furniture. 

                     

                  
 

                     
   
European Centre for Press and Media Freedom (2019), Greece: New democracy – new press freedom?

                     

                  
 

                     
   
